  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9. Respect of persons violates the command to love all alike \"as thyself.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "ye commit sin—literally, \"ye work sin,\" Mt 7:23, to which the reference here is probably, as in Jas 1:22. Your works are sin, whatever boast of the law ye make in words (see on [2604]Jas 2:8).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "convinced—Old English for \"convicted.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as transgressors—not merely of this or that particular command, but of the whole absolutely.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
